scenario:
No violation in the fragment as shown: check_apply_params simply calls check_param__epoll() and does not itself call itself. A Rule 17.2 violation would only occur if check_param__epoll (or a function it calls) called check_apply_params (directly or via a chain), e.g.:

static int check_param__epoll(void) { helper(); return 1; }
static void helper(void) { check_apply_params(); } 

This indirect call chain (check_apply_params -> check_param__epoll -> helper -> check_apply_params) would violate Rule 17.2.
